    "abstract": "We present a strategy to speed up Runge-Kutta-based ODE simulations of large systems with nearest-neighbor coupling. We identify the cache/memory bandwidth as the crucial performance bottleneck. To reduce the required bandwidth, we introduce a granularity in the simulation and identify the optimal cluster size in a performance study. This leads to a considerable performance increase and transforms the algorithm from bandwidth bound to CPU bound. By additionally employing SIMD instructions we are able to boost the efficiency even further. In the end, a total performance increase of up to a factor three is observed when using cache optimization and SIMD instructions compared to a standard implementation. All simulation codes are written in C++ and made publicly available. By using the modern C++ libraries this http URL and this http URL, these optimizations can be implemented with minimal programming effort.",
